-- Germany's Economy to Grow at Least 3% This Year, Minister Bruederle Says
-- B y   R a i n e r   B u e r g i n
-- 2010-10-18T06:56:05Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-18/germany-s-economy-to-grow-at-least-3-this-year-minister-bruederle-says.html
The German economy, Europe’s
largest, will expand at least 3 percent this year, Economy
Minister  Rainer Bruederle  said today on ZDF public television.  The government’s new economic forecast for this year, to be
published Oct. 21, will have “a three in front of the decimal
point,” Bruederle said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Rainer Buergin  in Berlin at 
 rbuergin1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Hertling at   jhertling@bloomberg.net  